        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 4:02PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 402 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Byers, or 38 miles southwest of Fort Morgan,
moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Leader.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rain is occurring with this storm and may lead to flooding. Do
not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
